# A generic function of dimension reduction which is used for Problem 1
def ThreeComponentPlot(feature, target, method, plot_dim="2D", scaling=True):
    # scaling the data as mu=0 and std=1 with normal assumption
    # number of principal component is 3
    if scaling==True:
        scaler = StandardScaler(with_mean=True, with_std=True)
        scaled_data = scaler.fit_transform(feature)
    else:
        # if no scaling, use feature matrix
        scaled_data = feature

    if method == "PCA":
        pca = PCA(n_components=3)
        x_pca = pca.fit_transform(scaled_data)
        xx = x_pca
        label = "principal component"
        print("Explained variance ratio: ", pca.explained_variance_ratio_)  
    if method == "MDS":
        model = MDS(n_components=3)
        x_mds = model.fit_transform(feature)
        xx = x_mds
        label = "MDS dimension"
    
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))
        
    if plot_dim == "3D":
        ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')
        ax.scatter(xx[:,0],xx[:,1],xx[:,2], c=target, cmap="plasma", s=60)
        ax.set_xlabel('First '+label)
        ax.set_ylabel('Second '+label)
        ax.set_ylabel('Third '+label)
    if plot_dim == "2D":
        fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows = 3, ncols = 1, sharex=True, sharey = True)

        axes[0].scatter(xx[:,0],xx[:,1],c=target,cmap='plasma')
        axes[0].set_xlabel('First '+label)
        axes[0].set_ylabel('Second '+label)

        axes[1].scatter(xx[:,0],xx[:,2],c=target,cmap='plasma')
        axes[1].set_xlabel('First '+label)
        axes[1].set_ylabel('Third '+label)

        axes[2].scatter(xx[:,1],xx[:,2],c=target,cmap='plasma')
        axes[2].set_xlabel('Second '+label)
        axes[2].set_ylabel('Third '+label)

        plt.subplots_adjust(hspace=0.2, top=6, bottom=0, left=0, right=1.5)
    
    return plt.show()

In [153]:
img_max = np.array([img[:,:,i].max() for i in range(3)])
In [154]:
# Create noised version of the image
img_noised = np.zeros((256,256,3))
for i in range(256):
    for j in range(256):
        for k in range(3):
            img_noised[i,j,k] = img[i,j,k] + uniform(img_min[k], img_max[k]*0.1)
In [155]:
# Plot noisy image and its RGB channels
fig, ax = plt.subplots(nrows = 2, ncols = 2, sharex=True, sharey = True, subplot_kw={'xticks':[], 'yticks':[]})

# Reconstruct pca components as images
fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 1, figsize=(10,10), subplot_kw={'xticks':[], 'yticks':[]})
for i, ax in enumerate(axes.flat):
    ax.imshow((df_gray_pca*pca.components_[i,:]).sum(axis = 1).values.reshape(232,232), cmap = 'gray')
    ax.set_title('Image Reconstruct from '+str(i+1)+'. Principal Component')
